genresAdvancedInfo.name: polyphonies corses
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Polyphonies corses, or Corsican polyphony, is a traditional music genre from the island of Corsica. It features multiple voices singing in harmony, often with no instrumental accompaniment. The songs are often sung in Corsican and feature themes of love, nature, and daily life on the island.
